#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga"
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38. Dutiyasūriyasutta → dutiyasuriyūpamasuttaṃ (bj) | suriyupamā 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Dutiyasūriyasutta"
msgstr "38. The Simile of the Sun (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, candimasūriyā loke nuppajjanti, neva tāva mahato "
"ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, as long as the moon and the sun don’t arise in the world, no "
"great light or great radiance appears."

#. VAR: Andhatamaṃ → andhantamaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.2"
msgid "Andhatamaṃ tadā hoti andhakāratimisā."
msgstr "Darkness prevails then, utter darkness."

#. VAR: rattindivā → rattidivā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn56.38:1.3"
msgid ""
"Neva tāva rattindivā paññāyanti, na māsaddhamāsā paññāyanti, na "
"utusaṃvaccharā paññāyanti."
msgstr ""
"Day and night aren’t found, nor months and fortnights, nor seasons and years."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.443"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.38:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, candimasūriyā loke uppajjanti, atha mahato ālokassa "
"pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa."
msgstr ""
"But when the moon and the sun arise in the world, a great light, a great "
"radiance appears."

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.2"
msgid "Neva andhakāratamaṃ tadā hoti na andhakāratimisā."
msgstr "Darkness no longer prevails."

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha rattindivā paññāyanti, māsaddhamāsā paññāyanti, utusaṃvaccharā "
"paññāyanti."
msgstr ""
"Day and night are found, and months and fortnights, and seasons and years."

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca tathāgato loke nuppajjati arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho, neva tāva mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, as long as the Realized One doesn’t arise in the world, no "
"great light or great radiance appears."

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.5"
msgid "Andhatamaṃ tadā hoti andhakāratimisā."
msgstr "Darkness prevails then, utter darkness."

msgctxt "sn56.38:2.6"
msgid ""
"Neva tāva catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhaṇā hoti desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā "
"vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There’s no explanation of the four noble truths, no teaching, advocating, "
"establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and revealing them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.38:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, atha "
"mahato ālokassa pātubhāvo hoti mahato obhāsassa."
msgstr ""
"But when the Realized One arises in the world, a great light, a great "
"radiance appears."

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.2"
msgid "Neva andhatamaṃ tadā hoti na andhakāratimisā."
msgstr "Darkness no longer prevails."

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ ācikkhaṇā hoti desanā paññāpanā paṭṭhapanā "
"vivaraṇā vibhajanā uttānīkammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then there’s the explanation of the four noble truths, the teaching, "
"advocating, establishing, clarifying, analyzing, and revealing them."

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.4"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.38:3.5"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya "
"ariyasaccassa."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.38:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.38:4.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
